abstract: >
  The TRIAD framework is a formally constrained epistemic architecture addressing
  meaning, measurement, and authority in multi-intelligence environments. It
  develops Relational Syntaxis (RS), Epistemological Special Relativity of
  Measurement Agents (ESRM), and Epistemic Measurement Dynamics (EMD), with
  applications to AI governance, irreversible records, and non-dominating
  institutional design.
